<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>4</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Ensure UKG access is provided to only those who really need it.&nbsp;(UK=
G Licensing - user counts)</p>
<p></p>
<p>Comments from Deloitte</p>
<p>=E2=80=93 Provisioning is not done by SailPoint.</p>
<p>=E2=80=93 Validate the user has account for that application.</p>
<p>=E2=80=93 Restrict on validation Request</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UKG has confirmed there is no correlation between our production UKG (Kr=
onos) Workforce Central (WFC) application user counts and our user counts f=
or our SaaS based Pro WFM (Voyager).&nbsp; That is, we can move forward wit=
h a reduction in contractual user counts for UKG Pro WFM without the need t=
o adjust what we are currently doing in production.</p>
<p>Given the current scope for UKG in Voyager (W2 Associates, Agency, and o=
ther NEPs that supervise W2 or Agency associates), <strong>we will official=
ly notify UKG of a reduction in user count to our contractual minimum of 15=
0k</strong> for UKG Pro WFM.&nbsp; (Please note that even if we were to inc=
lude Medxcel, R1, and Touchpoint into UKG, we have plenty of headroom; plea=
se feel free to verify through your own analytic sources.)</p>
<p>We do have to be more mindful of user counts in the future; there will a=
bsolutely be a production impact if we fail to manage this and exceed our c=
ounts.&nbsp; As part of governance, I would like to ensure that our upstrea=
m system (Oracle) is also carefully watching users counts and making projec=
tions so that we identify licensing adjustments and cost impacts in UKG bef=
ore they become an issue.</p>
<p>Ping me ASAP if you have any questions!</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Dallas</p></li>
</ul>
<p>--<br>
Dallas J. Mahnke | ERP Products</p>
<p>2050 Westport Center Drive&nbsp;| St. Louis, MO | 63146</p>
<p>Mobile - (248) 854-7782 | <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"mailto:dall=
as.mahnke@ascension.org" rel=3D"nofollow"><u>dallas.mahnke@ascension.org</u=
></a></p>
<p>Upcoming PTO and Holiday: April 18, May 26, June 23-27</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Open</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
